text: Turki Al Jalvan (; born 26 July 1991) is a Saudi Arabian professional footballer who plays as an Defender for Al-Nahda . ==Career== Al Jalvan began his career at the youth team of Al-Qaisumah and left the club and joined fellow Olympic team Al-Raed in 2010 . left Al-Raed and signed with Al-Batin in 2011 . left Al-Batin and signed with Al-Ittihad on May 20, 2015 left Al- Ittihad and signed with Al-Fateh on loan for the 2016–17 season on January 31, 2017 . He ended his contract with Al-Ittihad on January 6, 2019 . signed with Al-Qaisumah on February 27, 2019 . left Al-Qaisumah and signed with Al-Nahda on July 12, 2019 ==References== ==External links== * Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:Saudi Arabian footballers Category:Al-Qaisumah FC players Category:Al-Raed FC players Category:Al-Batin FC players Category:Ittihad FC players Category:Al-Fateh SC players Category:Al-Nahda Club (Saudi Arabia) players Category:Prince Mohammad bin Salman League players Category:Saudi Professional League players Category:Association football defenders
